The paper focuses on the advancement of artificial intelligence (AI) and intelligence augmentation (IA) for improved human-machine cognition in the context of multi-domain operations (MDO) and intelligence, surveillance, and reconnaissance (ISR) networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.AI, which deals with artificial intelligence and its applications. The paper also discusses human-machine teaming and collaboration, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of AI for distributed data analytics and dense urban terrain analysis suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper also touches on asset interoperability, which is related to robotics (cs.RO).
